Package: hsical
Title: Hyperspectral Image Calibration Tool
Version: 2.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Maurycy", "Żarczyński", , email = "maurycy.zarczynski@ug.edu.pl", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Claude", role = "ctb", comment = "Anthropic; two-mode v2.0 rebuild, single-scan v2.1"))
Description: A Shiny companion for hyperspectral scanning sessions. It treats
    every scan the same way, whether it was taken to test the geometry, to
    confirm it, or to keep: loading one capture header pulls in its white and
    dark references and its log, and the scan's motor positions, field of view
    and raster dimensions yield the along- and across-track pixel sizes, the
    aspect ratio, and the field of view that would square the pixels. Those
    derived values, together with operator input and header values, are written
    to an HSItools metadata sidecar, with a Review panel to read sidecars back.
    hsical owns no schema of its own; sidecar structure, serialization, and
    validation belong to HSItools.
